    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">The division of ‘quantity’ according to ‘kind of quantity’ is to some extent arbitrary</skos:scopeNote>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">In English, the terms for quantities in the left half of the table in 1.1, Note 1, are often used for the corresponding ‘kinds of quantity’. In French, the term “nature” is only used in expressions such as “grandeurs de même nature” (in English, “quantities of the same kind”).</skos:scopeNote>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Quantities of the same kind within a given system of quantities have the same quantity dimension. However, quantities of the same dimension are not necessarily of the same kind.</skos:scopeNote>
