    <skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">Kind</skos:altLabel>
    <skos:note xml:lang="en">The term "kind" is mainly used in expressions such as "quantities of the same kind." Two quantities of the same kind are mutually comparable, so that they can be placed in order of magnitude. Length and mass are quantities of different kinds because they are not mutually comparable.</skos:note>
